"{\"uid\": \"dailypost.ng-2024-08-10-paris-2024-olympics-team-nigeria-officially-finishes-without-single-medal\", \"text\": \"Published  on  By  Team Nigeria have officially finished its engagements at the 2024 Olympics in Paris, France, without winning a single medal.  Hannah Reuben was the last athlete left to salvage a medal for the West African nation.  But she lost her second round fight in the women's freestyle wrestling 76kg, losing 5-2 (Victory by points) to Mongolia's Davaanasan Amar Enkh.  This comes a day after Tobi Amusan failed to secure a place in the final of the women's 100m hurdles.  Nigeria's 4x400m men's relay team were also disqualified after their semi-final race.  It is Nogeria's worst outing at the Olympics since London 2012.  The next Olympics will be staged in Los Angeles in 2028.  EPL: Huge relief - Guardiola confirms Man City duo will not leave club this transfer window  Paris 2024 Olympics: Nigeria's last medal hope Reuben crashes out in Wrestling  Dantata gives reasons some Western nations equip bandits in Nigeria  Turkey: Victor Osimhen leaves Galatasaray, returns to Nigeria after injury  Super Eagles: Why I chose Nigeria over Germany - Maduka Okoye  Nigeria, UK seal agreements on migration, border security, business visas  Nigeria, Vietnam have highest fuel price hikes worldwide amid Iran, US-Israel war  ACF calls for overhaul of Nigeria's security strategy amid rising terror attacks  Copyright \\u00a9Daily Post Media Ltd\"}"